The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 November is 111,298 (12,827.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 November, there were 5,379 new confirmed cases (620.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 November, there were 4,928 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 9% (451 extra cases).
